a,b,c
a+b+c=3
 a+b+c \geq ab+bc+ca 
 \begin{align} a^2+b^2+c^2 &=\frac{a^2+b^2}{2}+\frac{b^2+c^2}{2}+\frac{a^2+c^2}{2} \geq \\ &\geq  \frac{2\sqrt{a^2b^2}}{2}+\frac{2\sqrt{b^2c^2}}{2}+\frac{2\sqrt{a^2c^2}}{2}= \\ &= ab+bc+ca \end{align} 
a+b+c=3
9=(a+b+c)^2=a^2+b^2+c^2+2(ab+bc+ca)\geq 3(ab+bc+ca)
9 = (a + b + c)^2 = a^2 + b^2 + c^2 + 2(ab+bc+ac) \geq 3(ab+bc + ac)
a+b+c=S
a=M+d \qquad b=M-d 
S  \ge M^2-d^2 + (S-2M)2M
 3M^2-2SM+S  +d^2  \ge 0 
S=3
3(M^2-2M+1)  +d^2  \ge 0 
3(M-1)^2 +d^2  \ge 0 
S=3
